The Dunning Kruger effect is often seen in different talent shows. For Example, American Idol or Britain’s Got Talent. The auditions show different people with varying performance levels. 
Those who get rejected, due to bad performances, often show emotions of disbelief or shock.
The bitter truth is that humans are not very good at evaluating themselves. Including you and me, the majority of people believe that they are better than others. 
Here are a few simple examples that will clarify your concept about the Dunning Kruger Effect.
In a study majority of elderly drivers believed that they were better drivers than others and in another study 94% percent of university professors believed that they were better than their colleagues.
